<subSubSection id="B5F66544FFFCCA78F812FAE229BFF89A" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="FD5336CFFFFCCA78F812FAE229BFF89A" blockId="2.[2022,2616,1355,1781]" lastBlockId="2.[1410,2619,1788,3320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="CF98EADDFFFCCA78F812FAE227B2FAB0" bold="true" box="[2022,2178,1355,1388]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="3AEC4D4CFFFCCA78F765FAE2265BFAB0" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[2193,2411,1355,1388]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasypodidae" genus="Dasypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cingulata" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" species="kappleri">Dasypus kappler</taxonomicName>
: Krauss, 1862, 
<materialsCitation id="4D843C92FFFCCA78F813FADB275AFA66" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3805309304" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">“den Urwaldern des Marowiniflusses in Surinam”</materialsCitation>
(= primeval forests near the Marowijne River, Suriname). 
<taxonomicName id="3AEC4D4CFFFCCA78F812FA4127F4F9D5" authorityName="Krauss" authorityYear="1862" box="[2022,2244,1512,1545]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasypodidae" genus="Dasypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cingulata" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kappleri">Dasypus kappleri</taxonomicName>
has been considered dis- tinct enough to warrant separation in its own subgenus, Hyperoambon; some have argued that this name should be elevated to a genus, but this has not been widely adopted. Others have proposed that the subspecies are distinct enough to be recognized as separate species, but this also has not been generally accepted. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B5F66544FFFCCA78FA77F8F929F8F785" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" type="synonymic_list">
<caption id="A9936647FFFCCA78FA77F8F929F8F785" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6631735" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6631735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6631735/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" targetBox="[1407,1999,1367,1781]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="FD5336CFFFFCCA78FA77F8F92823F8B1" blockId="2.[1410,2619,1788,3320]" box="[1411,1811,1872,1901]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="CF98EADDFFFCCA78FA77F8F92823F8B1" bold="true" box="[1411,1811,1872,1901]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">Subspecies and Distribution.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD5336CFFFFCCA78FA76F8DE278FF848" blockId="2.[1410,2619,1788,3320]" box="[1410,2239,1911,1940]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
