</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD5336CFFFFCCA78FA77F80B277CF83F" blockId="2.[1410,2619,1788,3320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName id="3AEC4D4CFFFCCA78FA77F80B281FF867" authority="Lonnberg, 1942" authorityName="Lonnberg" authorityYear="1942" box="[1411,1839,1954,1979]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasypodidae" genus="Dasypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cingulata" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="kappleri" subSpecies="beniensis">D.k.beniensisLonnberg,1942—lowlandsofAmazonianBrazilandBolivia,SoftheMadredeDios,Madeira,andlowerAmazonrivers.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD5336CFFFFCCA78FA77F84429F8F785" blockId="2.[1410,2619,1788,3320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName id="3AEC4D4CFFFCCA78FA77F8442837F7D6" authority="Thomas, 1901" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[1411,1799,2029,2058]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasypodidae" genus="Dasypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cingulata" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="kappleri" subSpecies="pastasae">D. k. pastasae Thomas, 1901</taxonomicName>
— E Andes Range of Colombia, Ecuador, and Peru, Venezuela, S of the Orinoco River, and W Amazon Basin in Brazil and NW Bolivia, N of the Rio Madre de Dios.
